Quick Install

1. Make sure that $HOME/bin is in your path:
    gedit ~/.bash_profile
        PATH=$PATH:$HOME/bin

2. Create a directory named "bin" on your home directory:
    mkdir ~/bin

3. Copy cscli there
    cp path/to/cscli ~/bin/

4. Give it safe permissions
    chmod 700 ~/bin/cscli

5. Edit it to so it haves your username and password
    CSAUTH=email@myisp.com:mySuper!D1ficult!.pa5sW0rd!

6. Refresh the environment!
    source ~/.bash_profile

7. Try
    cscli drives list

The API documentation can be found at: 
http://cloudsigma.com/en/platform-details/the-api

